getFinalPosition

public double[] getFinalPosition(Peak peak)
Return the position of the peak corrected for all errors and strains (look for a sample and call getFinalPosition(asample, peak, 0).

Parameters:
peak - the diffraction Peak for which the position is requested.

getFinalPosition

public double[] getFinalPosition(Sample asample,
                                 Peak peak,
                                 int computeStrain)
Return the position of the peak corrected for all errors and strains (it will call first the getCorrectedPosition(asample, position) and then will compute/retrieve the errors for strains/planar defects.

Parameters:
asample - the sample to which the datafile belong (considering the parent DataFileSet is active in that sample).
peak - the diffraction Peak for which the position is requested.
computeStrain - switch for computing strain displacement: 0 = use computed strain if any, 1 = use extracted strain directly if any, > 1 or < 0 don't use any strain to correct position.
